modules.description: handles HTTP method-specific service operations, including post, delete, put, and patch, with support for additional parameters in a dedicated payload. it defines functions that process requests and responses, enabling interaction with APIs beyond simple GET requests. operations include encoding and decoding payloads, managing request bodies, and handling method-specific data. examples include submitting form data via POST or updating resources with PUT.

Provides HTTP request methods like GET, POST, PUT, and PATCH with support for custom headers, request bodies, and chunked encoding. Operates on URI endpoints, HTTP methods, headers, and body streams, enabling interaction with web services and APIs. Handles both secure (TLS/SSL) and non-secure connections based on context configuration.

Handles HTTP request execution with customizable headers and body, using a specified HTTP method and URI. Operates on Cohttp header and body types, along with URI structures. Enables direct API calls in networked applications with fine-grained control over request parameters.

Provides functions to send HTTP requests with custom headers, bodies, and methods to a specified URI, returning a response and body wrapped in a Lwt promise. Operates with Cohttp's header and body types, along with HTTP methods and URIs. Used to construct HTTP client interactions in asynchronous Lwt-based applications.

Provides functions to define and handle HTTP/JSON RPC endpoints with type-safe request and response structures. Works with custom types representing service endpoints, request parameters, and JSON-encoded data. Used to build structured, compile-time verified RPC interfaces in applications like Tezos.

sends HTTP requests with customizable headers, bodies, and methods, returning responses and bodies as Lwt promises. It handles Cohttp's header and body types, HTTP methods, and URIs directly. Users can construct asynchronous HTTP interactions by specifying request details and processing the resulting data. Example tasks include fetching data from an API with custom headers or posting structured payloads to a server.
